cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about data-to-text generation using neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper compares two different architectures for this task: pipeline and end-to-end. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also uses deep learning methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the models using automatic and human evaluations, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
